            "header": "<strong>17. DISPUTE RESOLUTION</strong>",
            "text": "<p><strong>a. Federal Arbitration Act.</strong> The Federal Arbitration Act governs the interpretation and enforcement of this Section 17. This Section 17 evidences a transaction involving interstate commerce.<br/><strong>b. Informal Dispute Resolution;</strong> Pre-Arbitration Notice. The parties shall attempt in good faith to resolve any dispute arising out of or relating to these Terms by informal negotiation. As a condition precedent to commencing arbitration or any formal proceeding (other than an action permitted under Section 17(g)), you must first send a written description of your dispute to Mystery Tackle Box, Attn: Legal, 422 S Main St, Unit 2102, Lombard, IL 60148 (a “Notice of Dispute”). The Notice of Dispute must include your name, address, telephone number, email address, sufficient information to identify any transaction at issue, a detailed description of the dispute, and the nature and basis of your claims and the relief sought. The parties agree to negotiate in good faith, including through an informal and individualized telephone conference if requested by either party. If the dispute is not resolved within sixty (60) days after Mystery Tackle Box’s receipt of the Notice of Dispute, either party may proceed under the further dispute resolution provisions below. Any applicable limitations period and filing fee or other deadline will be tolled during this informal process.<br/><strong>c. Binding Arbitration</strong>; AAA Consumer Rules; Mass Arbitration Rules. Subject to Section 17(b), all claims and disputes in connection with these Terms or your use of any product or service provided by Mystery Tackle Box that cannot be resolved informally or in small claims court shall be resolved by binding arbitration on an individual basis. Arbitration shall be administered by the American Arbitration Association (“AAA”) in accordance with its Consumer Arbitration Rules and, if applicable, the AAA’s Mass Arbitration Supplementary Rules, except to the extent such rules conflict with this Section 17. The AAA’s rules are available at www.adr.org. The arbitration will be conducted by a single, neutral arbitrator. The award of the arbitrator will be accompanied by a reasoned opinion. Judgment on the award rendered by the arbitrator may be entered in any court of competent jurisdiction.<br/><strong>d. Non-Appearance Arbitration for Claims Under $10,000.</strong> For claims or disputes where the total amount of the award sought is less than Ten Thousand U.S. Dollars (US $10,000), the party seeking relief may elect non-appearance-based arbitration. If non-appearance arbitration is elected, the arbitration shall be conducted by telephone, online, and/or based solely on written submissions; the specific manner shall be chosen by the party initiating the arbitration. The arbitration shall not involve any personal appearance by the parties or witnesses unless mutually agreed.<br/><strong>e. Hearing Location</strong>. For any in-person hearing, the hearing will be held within one hundred (100) miles of your residence, unless you reside outside the United States (in which case the hearing will be held in the capital of your country), and unless the parties agree otherwise in writing.<br/><strong>f. Class Action and Representative Action Waiver;</strong> Jury Trial Waiver. You and Mystery Tackle Box each waive the right to a trial by jury and the right to participate as a plaintiff or class member in any purported class action, consolidated action, representative action, private attorney general action, or any other representative proceeding. We each agree that any dispute resolution proceedings will be conducted only on an individual basis and not in a class, consolidated or representative action. The arbitrator may not consolidate more than one person’s claims and may not otherwise preside over any form of class or representative proceeding. If this waiver is found to be unenforceable as to any particular dispute, then that dispute shall be resolved in court rather than in arbitration; this waiver shall otherwise remain in full force and effect.<br/><strong>g. Small Claims Court. </strong>Notwithstanding any other provision of this Section 17, either you or Mystery Tackle Box may bring an individual action in small claims court for any claim that qualifies for that court.<br/><strong>h. Equitable and Injunctive Relief. </strong>Notwithstanding the foregoing, either party may seek equitable or injunctive relief in any court of competent jurisdiction to enjoin a breach or threatened breach of any obligation under these Terms (including without limitation the misuse or infringement of intellectual property rights), without any requirement to post bond.<br/><strong>i. Confidentiality. The arbitration </strong>proceedings, including any evidence discovered or submitted at any hearing, shall be confidential and may not be disclosed except by written agreement of the parties, pursuant to court order, or as required by law. This subsection shall not prevent a party from submitting to a court information necessary to enforce this Section 17, to enforce an arbitration award, or to seek equitable or injunctive relief.<br/><strong>j. Opt-Out Right. </strong>You have the right to opt out of the arbitration provisions of this Section 17 (other than Section 17(f), which is non-severable) by sending written notice of your decision to opt out, postmarked within thirty (30) calendar days of your first acceptance of these Terms, to: Mystery Tackle Box, Attn: Legal, 422 S Main St, Unit 2102, Lombard, IL 60148. Your notice must include (i) your name and residence address, (ii) the email address and/or telephone number associated with your Account, and (iii) a clear statement that you want to opt out of the arbitration provisions of these Terms. If you opt out as set forth above, the remaining provisions of these Terms will continue to apply to you.<br/><strong>k. Severability and Survival.</strong> If any portion of this Section 17 is found to be invalid or unenforceable, that portion shall be severed and the remainder of this Section 17 shall remain in full force and effect, except as set forth in Section 17(f). This Section 17 will survive any termination of these Terms or your relationship with Mystery Tackle Box.<br/></p>",
